{"title":"Pässilä Juntu is the latest titanium downcountry hardtail mountain bike with sliding dropouts","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/11/passila-juntu-is-the-latest-titanium-downcountry-hardtail-mountain-bike-with-sliding-dropouts/","date":1636642562000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"passila juntu titanium downcountry hardtail frame with sliding dropouts\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11094409/passila-juntu-ti-hardtail-frame-only.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-278057\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Finnish bike manufacturer, Pässilä Bicycles, has today released a titanium downcountry hardtail named the Juntu. Designed for 120mm-130mm travel forks, the Juntu slots into their lineup as a more progressive version of the Kytö cross-country hardtail with lower, slacker, longer geometry, befitting to its downcountry intentions. Here’s a quick overview of the Pässilä Juntu.</p><h2>Pässilä Juntu Downcountry Hardtail</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only.jpg\" alt=\"passila juntu hardtail ti mtb downcountry geometry 120mm fork 29er\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093511/passila-junto-frame-only-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Like all Pässilä bicycles, the Juntu is a Grade 9 Titanium Alloy frame; this one weighs a claimed 2 kg in the largest size (S2). It is the first of their hardtails to feature sliding dropouts at the Boost rear end, allowing the fitment of a 27.5″ or 29″ rear wheel.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry.jpg\" alt=\"passila juntu sliding droputs ti mtb \" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093520/passila-junto-sliding-dropouts-ti-hardtail-mtb-downcountry-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Chainstay length is thus adjustable between 430mm and 450mm, offering a 20mm range of effective rear center lengths to suit different riding styles and different tire widths. The maximum tire clearance for a 29″ rear wheel is a claimed 2.6″, increasing to 2.8″ for a 27.5″.&nbsp;</p><div id=\"attachment_278159\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-278159\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail.jpg\" alt=\"passila juntu ti downcountry mtb 29er\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093524/passila-junto-ti-hardtail-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-278159\">The Juntu gets a 5-year frame warranty</p></div><p>While some of Pässilä’s other titanium hardtails are available in a complete size range, the Juntu is only available in two frame sizes, S1 and S2, catering to rider heights from 16ocm up to 185cm. The S1 gets a reach of 455m paired with a 400mm seat tube while the S2 gets a 485mm reach with a 420mm seat tube. The head angle is fairly slack at 65°, married to a 77° seat tube angle.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb.jpg\" alt=\"passila juntu geometry chart ti hardtail downcountry 29er\" width=\"1600\" height=\"927\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb-297x172.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb-800x464.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb-120x70.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb-768x445.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093516/passila-junto-geometry-chart-ti-downcountry-hardtail-mtb-1536x890.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The geometry quoted here is based on the Juntu running a complete 29″ wheelset and a 120mm travel suspension fork, though the frame is designed to handle up to a 130mm travel fork too.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike.jpg\" alt=\"passila juntu downcountry titanium hardtail mtb finnish\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11093529/passila-juntu-complete-bike-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The Pässilä Juntu is available to pre-order now at a price of €1999 incl. Finnish VAT 24%. with shipping available worldwide. Stock is due to arrive on January 15th, 2022.</p><p><a href=\"https://passilabicycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>PassilaBicycles.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4931b7433fc22e108570f0176aa0724e222bf543088bf98cf179a9b9d07b097a","category":"Cycling"}